Staff Management ‚Äã

The Staff Management panel allows server owners to add, edit, and remove dashboard staff members directly from the UI ‚Äî no server.cfg or config file editing required.

Accessing Staff Management ‚Äã

Navigate to System Settings in the sidebar. The Staff Management section is located between Appearance and Discord Integration.

IMPORTANT

Only users with the zcore.admin.settings permission can access the Staff Management panel.

Adding a Staff Member ‚Äã

  1. Click the "Add Staff" button
  2. Fill in the following fields:
FieldDescriptionExample
IdentifierAny FiveM identifierlicense:abc123, steam:110000112345678, discord:123456789
Display NameA human-readable nameModeratorMax
RoleCosmetic labelgod, admin, mod, supporter
  1. Toggle the permissions the staff member should have using the checkbox grid
  2. Optionally enable "Grant All (*)" for full access
  3. Click "Add Staff" to save

Supported Identifiers ‚Äã

All standard FiveM identifier types are supported:

  • license: ‚Äî Rockstar License
  • steam: ‚Äî Steam Hex ID
  • discord: ‚Äî Discord User ID
  • fivem: ‚Äî FiveM Account ID
  • ip: ‚Äî IP Address

The system loops through all of a player's identifiers at runtime. If any identifier matches a z_staff entry, the associated permissions are granted.

Managing Existing Staff ‚Äã

Each staff member row shows:

  • Avatar initials ‚Äî Auto-generated from their display name
  • Role badge ‚Äî Color-coded by role (gold for God, red for Admin, blue for Mod, green for Supporter)
  • Permission count ‚Äî Shows "All Perms" or the number of assigned permissions

Actions ‚Äã

  • Expand (‚ñº) ‚Äî Click to reveal all assigned permissions as badges
  • Edit (‚úèÔ∏è) ‚Äî Opens the form pre-filled with the member's current data
  • Delete (üóëÔ∏è) ‚Äî Removes the staff member from the database

How Permissions Merge at Runtime ‚Äã

When a player opens the dashboard, Z-Core evaluates permissions from three sources:

1. ACE Principals (server.cfg)     ‚Üí checked via IsPlayerAceAllowed()
2. Config Mappings (config.ts)     ‚Üí checked via IsPlayerAceAllowed()
3. Staff Database (z_staff table)  ‚Üí checked via getPlayerIdentifiers()

All three are merged into a single permissions[] array. This means:

  • A player can have ACE permissions AND database permissions ‚Äî they stack
  • Removing a z_staff entry only removes database-granted permissions
  • ACE/Config permissions remain unaffected
